  <strong>Concept Sketching Technique</strong>

  <ol>
    <li>Pencil: construction lines</li>
    <li>Finest pen: visible lines</li>
    <li>Medium pen: outlines of important features</li>
    <li>Heavier pen: overall outline of the entire object</li>
    <li>Heaviest pen: outline ‘shadow’ on lower edges</li>
    <li>Fine detail: ink in more detail using fine pen</li>
    <li>Gray-scale shadows: simple shadows on object</li>
    <li>Background: spatial reference rectangle behind the object</li>
    <li>Shadow on background: give sense of 3D</li>
    <li>Colour wash: one colour with marker</li>
    <li>Highlights: apex of areas in light</li>
    <li>Colour detail: highlight features</li>
  </ol>

